    "reasoning": "1. **Analyze the State Machine Requirements**: The Lemming has several behaviors: walking (left or right), falling (aaah!), and digging. These behaviors are interconnected. The state needs to track both the current direction (left/right) and the current activity (walking, falling, or digging).\n\n2. **Identify States**:\n    - `WALK_LEFT`: Walking left on ground.\n    - `WALK_RIGHT`: Walking right on ground.\n    - `FALLING_L`: Falling after being in `WALK_LEFT` (to remember direction).\n    - `FALLING_R`: Falling after being in `WALK_RIGHT` (to remember direction).\n    - `DIGGING_L`: Digging while moving left.\n    - `DIGGING_R`: Digging while moving right.\n    - `FALLING_DIG_L`: Falling after digging while moving left.\n    - `FALLING_DIG_R`: Falling after digging while moving right.\n\n3. **Define Transitions**:\n    - **From WALK_LEFT**:\n        - If `ground == 0` -> `FALLING_L` (aaah).\n        - Else if `dig == 1` -> `DIGGING_L` (digging).\n        - Else if `bump_right == 1` -> `WALK_RIGHT` (switch direction).\n        - Else if `bump_left == 1` -> `WALK_LEFT` (stay).\n        - (Note: Priority order: Fall > Dig > Bump).\n    - **From WALK_RIGHT**:\n        - If `ground == 0` -> `FALLING_R` (aaah).\n        - Else if `dig == 1` -> `DIGGING_R` (digging).\n        - Else if `bump_left == 1` -> `WALK_LEFT` (switch direction).\n        - Else if `bump_right == 1` -> `WALK_RIGHT` (stay).\n    - **From DIGGING_L/R**:\n        - If `ground == 0` -> `FALLING_DIG_L/R` (aaah, then fall).\n        - Else -> stay in `DIGGING_L/R`.\n    - **From FALLING_L/R/DIG_L/R**:\n        - If `ground == 1` -> return to `WALK_L/R` or `WALK_L/R` (depending on direction).\n\n4. **Moore Output Mapping**:\n    - `walk_left`: True in `WALK_LEFT`.\n    - `walk_right`: True in `WALK_RIGHT`.\n    - `aaah`: True in `FALLING_L`, `FALLING_R`, `FALLING_DIG_L`, `FALLING_DIG_R`.\n    - `digging`: True in `DIGGING_L`, `DIGGING_R`.\n\n5. **Advice to avoid syntax errors**:\n    - Always use `always @(*)` for combinational logic to avoid missing signals in the sensitivity list.\n    - Use `always @(posedge clk or posedge areset)` for asynchronous reset logic.\n    - Ensure all paths in a `case` statement are covered or provide a `default` to prevent unintended latches.\n    - Use `logic` instead of `reg` for modern SystemVerilog style.",
    "module": "module TopModule(\n    input  logic clk,\n    input  logic areset,\n    input  logic bump_left,\n    input  logic bump_right,\n    input  logic ground,\n    input  logic dig,\n    output logic walk_left,\n    output logic walk_right,\n    output logic aaah,\n    output logic digging\n);\n\n    // State encoding\n    localparam WALK_LEFT         = 4'd0;\n    localparam WALK_RIGHT        = 4'd1;\n    localparam FALLING_L        = 4'd2;\n    localparam FALLING_R        = 4'd3;\n    localparam DIGGING_L        = 4'd4;\n    localparam DIGGING_R        = 4'd5;\n    localparam FALLING_DIG_L    = 4'd6;\n    localparam FALLING_DIG_R    = 4'd7;\n\n    logic [3:0] state;\n    logic [3:0] next_state;\n\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset) begin\n            state <= WALK_LEFT;\n        end else begin\n            state <= next_state;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state\n    always @(*) begin\n        next_state = state;\n        case (state)\n            WALK_LEFT:\n                if (!ground)          next_state = FALLING_L;\n                else if (dig)         next_state = DIGGING_L;\n                else if (bump_right)  next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n                else if (bump_left)   next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n\n            WALK_RIGHT:\n                if (!ground)          next_state = FALLING_R;\n                else if (dig)         next_state = DIGGING_R;\n                else if (bump_left)   next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n                else if (bump_right)  next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n\n            DIGGING_L:\n                if (!ground)          next_state = FALLING_DIG_L;\n                else                  next_state = DIGGING_L;\n\n            DIGGING_R:\n                if (!ground)          next_state = FALLING_DIG_R;\n                else                  next_state = DIGGING_R;\n\n            FALLING_L:\n                if (ground)           next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n                else                  next_state = FALLING_L;\n\n            FALLING_R:\n                if (ground)           next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n                else                  next_state = FALLING_R;\n\n            FALLING_DIG_L:\n                if (ground)           next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n                else                  next_state = FALLING_DIG_L;\n\n            FALLING_DIG_R:\n                if (ground)           next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n                else                  next_state = FALLING_DIG_R;\n\n            default:\n                next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Moore Output Logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        walk_left = 1'b0;\n        walk_right = 1'b0;\n        aaah = 1'b0;\n        digging = 1'b0;\n\n        case (state) \n            WALK_LEFT:\n                walk_left = 1'b1;\n            WALK_RIGHT:\n                walk_right = 1'b1;\n            DIGGING_L:\n                digging = 1'b1;\n            DIGGING_R:\n                digging = 1'b1;\n            FALLING_L,\n            FALLING_R,\n            FALLING_DIG_L,\n            FALLING_DIG_R:\n                aaah = 1'b1;\n            default:\n                begin\n                    walk_left = 1'b0;\n                    walk_right = 1'b0;\n                    aaah = 1'b0;\n                    digging = 1'b0;\n                end\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
